<paragraph blockId="22.[264,1323,284,510]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
On Jerzy Proszynski’s web site (
<bibRefCitation author="Proszynski" box="[707,911,284,310]" pageId="22" pageNumber="37" refString="Proszynski, J. (2003) Salticidae (Araneae) of the world. http: // salticidae. org / salticid / main. htm. Accessed on December 23 rd 2005." type="book chapter" year="2003">
Proszynski 
<number box="[848,911,284,310]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[934,1080,284,309]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Pellenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanus">
<emphasis box="[934,1080,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">P. montanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is listed as a junior synonym of the Palearctic species 
<taxonomicName authority="Sundevall 1833" authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1833" box="[672,1044,324,350]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Pellenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lapponicus">
<emphasis box="[672,830,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">P. lapponicus</emphasis>
(Sundevall 
<number box="[972,1034,324,350]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="1833.0">1833</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but that synonymy has never been officially published. Illustrations provided on this web site show small differences in the spermathecae between Palearctic and Nearctic specimens. We prefer to use 
<taxonomicName box="[312,456,444,469]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Pellenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanus">
<emphasis box="[312,456,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">P. montanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for specimens collected in North 
<collectingCountry box="[861,962,444,470]" name="United States of America" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">America</collectingCountry>
until that question is formally addressed.
</paragraph>
